## Create a Specific Order Product


```shell
curl "<%= config[:endpoint] %>orderProduct" \\
  -X POST \\
  -H "Accept: application/vnd.api+json" \\
  -H "Authorization: Bearer <%= config[:example_token] %>" \\
  -H "Content-Type: application/vnd.api+json" \\
  -d '{
        "data": {
          "type": "orderProduct", 
          "attributes": {
            "totalOrdered": 5
          },
          "relationships": {
            "order": {
              "data": {
                "type": "order",
                "id": "<%= config[:example_order] %>"
              }
            },
            "product": {
              "data": {
                "type": "product",
                "id": "<%= config[:example_product] %>"
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }'
```

> If successful, the above command returns the modified resource in the same structure as `GET`

This endpoint creates and retrieves a specified `orderProduct`.

